%N A359096 The sum of the numbers on the perimeter of the n X n diamond frame, located at the top of the numerical pyramid containing the positive integers in natural order.
%C A359096 The numerical pyramid is constructed from natural numbers as follows: the first line contains the number 1, the second line contains the numbers 2 and 3, the third line contains the next three numbers, and so on.
%H A359096 Nicolay Avilov, <a href="/A359096/a359096.jpg">Square frames for a(1) - a(6)</a>
%H A359096 Nicolay Avilov, <a href="https://elementy.ru/problems/2371/Piramida_s_ramkoy">Pyramid with frame</a> (in Russian).
%H A359096 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (4,-6,4,-1).
%F A359096 a(n) = (8*n^3 - 12*n^2 + 13*n - 9)/3, where n > 1.
%F A359096 G.f.: x*(1 + 7*x + 8*x^2 - x^3 + x^4)/(1 - x)^4. - _Stefano Spezia_, Dec 16 2022
%e A359096 For n = 4 we have a numerical pyramid with numbers from 1 to 36 and its diamond frame, and the sum of the numbers that lie along the frame is a(4):
%e A359096 .
%e A359096                1
%e A359096               / \
%e A359096              2   3
%e A359096             /     \
%e A359096            4   5   6
%e A359096           /         \
%e A359096          7   8   9  10
%e A359096           \         /
%e A359096       11  12  13  14  15
%e A359096             \     /
%e A359096     16  17  18  19  20  21
%e A359096               \ /
%e A359096   22  23  24  25  26  27  28
%e A359096 .
%e A359096 a(4) = 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 6 + 7 + 10 + 12 + 14 + 18 + 19 + 25 = 121.
